entries.femaleVariant: Agh! W-what's that?  Legs getting... tired?
Quit cryin', your majesty! Or I'll cut our your tongue!
Where's the cash?! Don't play me!
The fuck're you?
The hell d'you want? Jealous of his majesty's busted ribs?
Agreed.
I need details first.
Kendachi's infamous for its suicides.
I'm supposed to explain her decision?
Is that--agh! T-that all you got?
Heard you talkin' in your sleep!
Plenty more to go 'round!
Enid's dream project?
Corpo-prick drifted off. Musta really drilled it into him, the corp's glorious vision. Till he grew a heart, anyway.
Think this daughter issue was what wrecked the guy?
That was rhetorical right? You really gotta work on your intonation.
Shame he didn't finish his story. Actually had me curious what he wanted to ask – and what happened to Enid.
On the edge of your seat, huh?
Ugh... Bravo. What an altruist. What do ya want now? Warm hug? Handful of ennies?
You needed help.
You owe me.
That why you were hollerin'? 'Cause you didn't "have a stake in it?"
A few ennies sounds nice, actually. Your choombas mentioned a hidden stash.
How 'bout some advice instead. You see someone not asking for help... you keep walkin'.
Neither side... had any real stake in it.
The body... doesn't always do what it's told. Not even implants always help... Pain is pain.
My "choombas" think they're smarter than me. But they're easy to mislead... to manipulate.
Not your average homeless guy, are you?
You were provoking them?
Hold up... You wanted to provoke them? On purpose?
Does it matter? Why do you care?
Normally, I'd say "'cause I saved your ass," but I'm guessin' that won't do the trick.
You're starting to catch on.
Not a man of the streets, are you? Where'd you drop in from?
Actually, think you do owe me.
Two bums kick your ass to the curb, you're insulted that I'd dare help, and now you try to chew me out with perfect diction.
Actually, think I am owed.
Didn't think anyone would notice?
What is it to you? I owe you shit. Now, leave me alone.
I dunno how you ruffled their rags, but seemed pretty clear to me you weren't gettin' kicked by choice.
If you thought none of that'd seem odd, ya didn't quite think it through.
Hm. You're stubborn – just like my daughter. She loved to call people out on their gaps in logic.
Actually... You even look her age...
All right, fine. I'll satisfy your curiosity provided you do something for me later on. Are we agreed?
C'mon, out with it. Who are you really?
A deal with details in the dark? Consider me interested.
Nice try. You spin some tall tale and then I have to do... Jesus, I don't even wanna think what.
I'll hold you to your word. In the meantime, I invite you to my cozy abode. Need to get off my feet – I can barely stand.
No, you tell me you story and what it is you want from me, then I make my decision.
Got a real negotiator on my hands, huh... So be it, follow me. Need to get off my feet , after all. I can barely stand.
Now? Nobody. But a few months ago, a seat on the Kendachi board had my name on it – Ken Lee.
My, my! What an honor! Got someone you owe to this spectacular downfall?
No, no one. I sacrificed my life for the company. And I wanted my daughter... Enid... to do the same.
Daddy plannin' out his kid's career? Rings of domestic despot to me...
Wrong again. Biotech was Enid's passion. And at Kendachi, she could make her living immersed in it.
I just wanted her to be happy. Does that make me a rotten father? Does it?!
If my dad micromanaged my whole life, I'd've bail first chance I got and never looked back.
Just matched her own plans with your expectations. Nothin' wrong in that.
Wouldn't want a dad like you.
You did nothing wrong.
I gave her everything! Toys, books, even a dog! Do you know how steep the taxes on those fleabags are?
And this gives you the right to control her life?
Think we got off subject...
I'm sure your family history's a real page-turner, but what's it got to do with your hero-to-zero story?
I'll get to that. But first, you answer my question.
What, whether you're a shitty dad? What do you care what I think?
What do you care about my story?
She'd have equipment, resources... One month and I could give her an entire lab at Kendachi to lead.
Everything she could need to carry out her dream project.... So why'd she choose Biotechnica?
Exactly! I gave her everything! Toys, books, even a dog! Do you know how steep the taxes on those fleabags are?
A good dad, and a corpo no less.
What's this dream project of hers?
Well... Enid always loved nature's strangest creatures. As a girl, she wanted to bring the platypus back from extinction.
Not foxes or bears, but platypuses specifically. She was a special kid.
Platy--what? That alien or animal?
It's like a cross between a duck and a beaver. Can you imagine? I'd love to see one with own two eyes.
Maybe she didn't want to be a martyr for some deadline deity. Kendashi's got a nasty rep for staff suicides.
Wait, you... you want me to explain why your daugher jumped ship for the competition?
Eighteen-hour workdays can break a man's soul... Or his family's, at the very least.
You think think it's that simple? That...that you just quit and live happily ever after?
I did. Dunno if it extended my life any, but I like to think my mood's taken a turn for the better.
Don't have any kids, do you? Well, without my money, Enid could only ever dream of becoming a bioengineer!
Didn't consider that, did you? Like the eddies just fell from the sky, and I spent my nights in meetings by choice! I did it all for her!
Hey, Ken... Maybe get off my back?
I did everything to convince her. The problem was with her... Right? It must've been!
Take it easy, man. How could I know...
I had to the right to feel betrayed. Who keeps traitors close? Suicidal fools, that's who!
S-she made... her decision... She knew... Kendachi is my life. So why... why would...
Ugh... Think my kidneys got the worst of it.
Yo, Ken. You alive?
Look like a gonk when you smile. Nah, I just love seein' bottomed-out corpos – balm for the soul. Curious how he wound up here.
Guess we gotta wait for the exciting conclusion.
Did she know anyone at Biotechnica?
Guessin' she didn't know anyone at Biotechnica, did she?
Not that I know of. Why?
If I were her, wouldn't want anyone thinkin' I got my job 'cause I'm daddy's pet.
Anywhere else she has to rely on herself. An uphill climb, sure, but all the more satisfying.
